Comment: 0,0:00:04.24,0:00:05.64,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,字幕
Dialogue: 0,0:00:04.24,0:00:05.64,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}Hello it's Scott Manley here.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:04.24,0:00:05.64,1080P-sgsm-63,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}你好 我是Scott Manley
Dialogue: 0,0:00:05.83,0:00:10.63,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}I love to talk about space hardware and this usually means rockets and spaceships
Dialogue: 0,0:00:05.83,0:00:10.63,1080P-sgsm-63,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}我喜欢谈论航天设备 这通常是指火箭和飞船
Dialogue: 0,0:00:10.63,0:00:15.73,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}but sometimes there are more mundane everyday items used in spaceflight.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:10.63,0:00:15.73,1080P-sgsm-63,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}但是更多平凡的日常用品也会用于航天活动当中
Dialogue: 0,0:00:15.97,0:00:21.27,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}In fact one of the most significant things brought to space on John Glenn's first orbital flight
Dialogue: 0,0:00:15.97,0:00:21.27,1080P-sgsm-63,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}其实在约翰·格伦的第一次入轨飞行中 被带入太空的最重要的东西之一是
Dialogue: 0,0:00:21.69,0:00:23.81,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}was something that he bought in a store.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:21.69,0:00:23.81,1080P-sgsm-63,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}他在一家商店买的东西
Dialogue: 0,0:00:24.40,0:00:28.85,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}This was the camera which he used to take some of the historic photos of earth.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:24.40,0:00:28.85,1080P-sgsm-63,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}这是他用来拍摄一些闻名历史的地球照片的相机
Dialogue: 0,0:00:29.47,0:00:32.71,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}As I understand it John Glenn bought the camera on his own
Dialogue: 0,0:00:29.47,0:00:32.71,1080P-sgsm-63,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}据我所知 约翰·格伦是单独买的相机
Dialogue: 0,0:00:32.71,0:00:37.28,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}because he was concerned that there might be delays in getting something approved for flight
Dialogue: 0,0:00:32.71,0:00:37.28,1080P-sgsm-63,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}因为他担心在获得飞行许可方面可能会出现延误
Dialogue: 0,0:00:37.33,0:00:40.55,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}if he went through the regular government acquisitions process.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:37.33,0:00:40.55,1080P-sgsm-63,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}如果他要通过常规的政府采购程序来购买这个设备
Dialogue: 0,0:00:41.03,0:00:46.74,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}I'm not sure why the mission planners hadn't considered a regular camera early in the process.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:41.03,0:00:46.74,1080P-sgsm-63,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}我不知道为什么任务规划者在计划的初期 没有考虑使用普通相机
Dialogue: 0,0:00:47.03,0:00:48.28,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}Perhaps they'd left it out
Dialogue: 0,0:00:47.03,0:00:48.28,1080P-sgsm-63,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}也许他们是觉得没必要
Dialogue: 0,0:00:48.31,0:00:52.80,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}because there was a science experiment involving another modified camera on the same flight.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:48.31,0:00:52.80,1080P-sgsm-63,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}因为在同一次飞行中 有个科学实验使用了另一个改装过的相机
Dialogue: 0,0:00:53.19,0:00:57.42,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}Or it's possible that because the early automated flights in the Mercury program
Dialogue: 0,0:00:53.19,0:00:57.42,1080P-sgsm-63,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}也有可能是因为早期的水星计划中的自动飞行
Dialogue: 0,0:00:57.42,0:01:00.51,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}had included cameras that took lots of photos of the earth
Dialogue: 0,0:00:57.42,0:01:00.51,1080P-sgsm-63,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}包含了相机 并拍摄了大量的地球照片
Dialogue: 0,0:01:00.71,0:01:07.03,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}that maybe they couldn't see the advantage in having a human holding a camera and pointing it themselves.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:00.71,0:01:07.03,1080P-sgsm-63,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}这使得他们看不到人拿着相机拍摄的优势
Dialogue: 0,0:01:07.92,0:01:09.92,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}So yeah John Glenn's camera.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:07.92,0:01:09.92,1080P-sgsm-63,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}那么 没错 约翰·格伦的相机
Dialogue: 0,0:01:09.92,0:01:13.95,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}It was an Ansco auto set 35 millimeter camera
Dialogue: 0,0:01:09.92,0:01:13.95,1080P-sgsm-63,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}这是一个Ansco自动设置35毫米相机
Dialogue: 0,0:01:13.95,0:01:18.83,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}which was actually a re-badged version of the first Minolta Hi-Matic.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:13.95,0:01:18.83,1080P-sgsm-63,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}这实际上是第一台美能达Hi-Matic相机的重新贴牌版本
Dialogue: 0,0:01:19.20,0:01:24.45,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}So this was the first Minolta rangefinder camera with automatic exposure.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:19.20,0:01:24.45,1080P-sgsm-63,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}那么这是第一台具有自动曝光功能的美能达Rangefinder相机
Dialogue: 0,0:01:24.46,0:01:30.62,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}So it would set both the aperture and the shutter speed using a built-in selenium light meter.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:24.46,0:01:30.62,1080P-sgsm-63,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}那么它可以通过一个内置的硒测光表来设置光圈和快门速度
Dialogue: 0,0:01:31.28,0:01:35.36,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}And this automation would obviously make it good for use in flight
Dialogue: 0,0:01:31.28,0:01:35.36,1080P-sgsm-63,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}这种自动化显然使它适合在飞行中使用
Dialogue: 0,0:01:35.43,0:01:38.20,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}when you know John would have his suit on
Dialogue: 0,0:01:35.43,0:01:38.20,1080P-sgsm-63,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}也就是约翰穿着宇航服的时候
Dialogue: 0,0:01:38.20,0:01:43.37,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}and he'd have limited chance to adjust the controls and possibly also be busy with other things.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:38.20,0:01:43.37,1080P-sgsm-63,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}这时他不太可能去调整控制 而且还会忙于其他事情
Dialogue: 0,0:01:44.00,0:01:49.04,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}Now to make the camera usable in space NASA engineers took it and they modified it.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:44.00,0:01:49.04,1080P-sgsm-63,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}那么 为了使相机能在太空中使用 NASA的工程师们对它进行了改造
Dialogue: 0,0:01:49.04,0:01:53.36,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}They flipped the whole camera upside down and they added a pistol grip
Dialogue: 0,0:01:49.04,0:01:53.36,1080P-sgsm-63,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}他们把整个相机翻转过来 并加了一个手枪握把
Dialogue: 0,0:01:53.36,0:01:57.27,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}with thumb paddles that would actuate the shutter and film winding controls.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:53.36,0:01:57.27,1080P-sgsm-63,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}这样可以用拇指拨片来驱动快门和胶卷过片控制
Dialogue: 0,0:01:57.28,0:01:59.91,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}These connected physically to the controls on the camera.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:57.28,0:01:59.91,1080P-sgsm-63,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}这些都与相机上的控制装置相连
Dialogue: 0,0:02:00.07,0:02:03.73,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}Now they also needed a viewfinder so they added that on the top
Dialogue: 0,0:02:00.07,0:02:03.73,1080P-sgsm-63,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}现在他们还需要一个取景器 所以他们把它加在了相机的顶部
Dialogue: 0,0:02:03.75,0:02:06.02,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}which of course would now be on the bottom.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:03.75,0:02:06.02,1080P-sgsm-63,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}当然 现在则会在底部
Dialogue: 0,0:02:06.40,0:02:10.84,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}But that would also be helpful because it could be used with the suit helmet closed.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:06.40,0:02:10.84,1080P-sgsm-63,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}但这也会很有帮助 因为它可以在关上宇航服头盔玻璃罩的情况下使用
Dialogue: 0,0:02:11.77,0:02:14.43,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}The other camera on the flight was a Leica
Dialogue: 0,0:02:11.77,0:02:14.43,1080P-sgsm-63,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}飞行中使用的另一台相机是徕卡的
Dialogue: 0,0:02:14.64,0:02:16.72,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}which had been modified for a science experiment.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:14.64,0:02:16.72,1080P-sgsm-63,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}这是为科学实验而改装的
Dialogue: 0,0:02:16.72,0:02:21.68,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}It had been given quartz optics and a prism to perform spectroscopy on stars
Dialogue: 0,0:02:16.72,0:02:21.68,1080P-sgsm-63,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}在其上安装了石英光学元件和棱镜 以对恒星进行光谱分析
Dialogue: 0,0:02:22.11,0:02:27.13,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}so the experiment would involve taking photos of stars in the constellation of Orion
Dialogue: 0,0:02:22.11,0:02:27.13,1080P-sgsm-63,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}那么实验就需要拍摄猎户座星座中的恒星照片
Dialogue: 0,0:02:27.36,0:02:31.28,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}and the light from these stars would be dispersed by a prism allowing the spectra to be seen.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:27.36,0:02:31.28,1080P-sgsm-63,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}而这些恒星发出的光会被棱镜分散 从而使光谱得以显现
Dialogue: 0,0:02:31.33,0:02:35.00,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}But because these images were being taken in space
Dialogue: 0,0:02:31.33,0:02:35.00,1080P-sgsm-63,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}但由于这些图像是在太空中拍摄的
Dialogue: 0,0:02:35.20,0:02:38.08,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}the spectrum would stretch into the ultraviolet region,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:35.20,0:02:38.08,1080P-sgsm-63,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}频谱将延伸到紫外线区域
Dialogue: 0,0:02:38.48,0:02:43.10,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}an area of the spectrum which is on the inaccessible to ground-based astronomy.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:38.48,0:02:43.10,1080P-sgsm-63,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}而这个区域是地基天文学无法获得的
Dialogue: 0,0:02:43.51,0:02:46.23,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}Now I'm sure there's a lot of you out here by the way right now
Dialogue: 0,0:02:43.51,0:02:46.23,1080P-sgsm-63,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}那么我相信你们中的很多人在这儿会说
Dialogue: 0,0:02:46.23,0:02:50.76,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}who are making comments about how John Glenn wasn't the first space traveler with a camera.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:46.23,0:02:50.76,1080P-sgsm-63,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}约翰·格伦并不是第一个带相机的太空旅行者
Dialogue: 0,0:02:51.18,0:02:56.94,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}Because of course on Vostok 2 Gherman Titov carried a Soviet Konvas movie camera
Dialogue: 0,0:02:51.18,0:02:56.94,1080P-sgsm-63,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}因为在东方二号上 没错 是戈尔曼·季托夫 他携带了苏联的Konvas电影摄像机
Dialogue: 0,0:02:57.20,0:02:59.08,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}had about 300 meters of film
Dialogue: 0,0:02:57.20,0:02:59.08,1080P-sgsm-63,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}还有大概300米长的胶卷
Dialogue: 0,0:02:59.13,0:03:03.89,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}and I hear that during the launch the exposure setting dial broke.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:59.13,0:03:03.89,1080P-sgsm-63,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}而我听说在发射过程中 曝光设置盘坏了
Dialogue: 0,0:03:04.23,0:03:07.68,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}So Titov pretty much had to guess his way through the exposures
Dialogue: 0,0:03:04.23,0:03:07.68,1080P-sgsm-63,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}所以季托夫只好猜测他的曝光方式
Dialogue: 0,0:03:07.74,0:03:10.09,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}but he did a pretty good job
Dialogue: 0,0:03:07.74,0:03:10.09,1080P-sgsm-63,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}但他做得很好
Dialogue: 0,0:03:10.10,0:03:13.68,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}and these are the first images taken by a human in space.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:10.10,0:03:13.68,1080P-sgsm-63,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}而这些都是人类在太空中拍摄的第一张照片
Dialogue: 0,0:03:13.92,0:03:15.51,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}Gagarin didn't fly with a camera
Dialogue: 0,0:03:13.92,0:03:15.51,1080P-sgsm-63,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}加加林飞行的时候没带相机
Dialogue: 0,0:03:15.51,0:03:19.29,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}so he could only describe what it looked like over radio.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:15.51,0:03:19.29,1080P-sgsm-63,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}所以他只能通过无线电描述太空的样子
Dialogue: 0,0:03:19.59,0:03:23.92,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}I'd love to talk more about russian cameras but I don't actually have any sources.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:19.59,0:03:23.92,1080P-sgsm-63,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}我很想多说一些关于俄罗斯相机的事情 但我实际上没有任何资料来源
Dialogue: 0,0:03:24.00,0:03:26.31,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}So I'm going to focus on the US side of things.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:24.00,0:03:26.31,1080P-sgsm-63,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}那么我将专注于美国这边
Dialogue: 0,0:03:26.91,0:03:28.73,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}And on the US side of things
Dialogue: 0,0:03:26.91,0:03:28.73,1080P-sgsm-63,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}而在美国这边
Dialogue: 0,0:03:28.95,0:03:33.86,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}Wally Schirra would be the one to set the future standard for space photography gear.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:28.95,0:03:33.86,1080P-sgsm-63,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}沃利·施艾拉将成为未来太空摄影设备的标准制定者
Dialogue: 0,0:03:34.20,0:03:41.82,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}When he took a Hasselblad 500C camera on six orbits around the earth in his Mercury capsule sigma seven.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:34.20,0:03:41.82,1080P-sgsm-63,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}当他带着哈苏500C相机在水星太空舱的西格玛7号上绕地球六圈时
Dialogue: 0,0:03:42.01,0:03:44.86,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}Apparently Wally was a bit of a shutterbug
Dialogue: 0,0:03:42.01,0:03:44.86,1080P-sgsm-63,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}显然 沃利有点摄影迷
Dialogue: 0,0:03:44.93,0:03:46.92,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}and when he was preparing for his mission
Dialogue: 0,0:03:44.93,0:03:46.92,1080P-sgsm-63,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}而当他准备执行任务的时候
Dialogue: 0,0:03:47.20,0:03:52.56,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}he asked professional photographers who'd been following the Mercury program, you know, advice.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:47.20,0:03:52.56,1080P-sgsm-63,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}他咨询了那些一直关注着水星计划的专业摄影师的意见
Dialogue: 0,0:03:52.57,0:03:58.88,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}And based on their advice he bought this Hasselblad camera at a houston photo supply store
Dialogue: 0,0:03:52.57,0:03:58.88,1080P-sgsm-63,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}根据他们的建议 他在休斯敦的一家摄影用品店买了这台哈苏相机
Dialogue: 0,0:03:59.20,0:04:01.88,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}along with lenses and film magazines.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:59.20,0:04:01.88,1080P-sgsm-63,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}以及镜头和胶卷盒
Dialogue: 0,0:04:02.00,0:04:04.48,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}So the Hasselblad was a medium format camera.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:02.00,0:04:04.48,1080P-sgsm-63,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}那么哈苏是一款中画幅相机
Dialogue: 0,0:04:04.48,0:04:08.15,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}It exposed a much larger area four times the area of film
Dialogue: 0,0:04:04.48,0:04:08.15,1080P-sgsm-63,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}它的曝光面积是电影胶片的四倍
Dialogue: 0,0:04:08.15,0:04:10.84,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}and that meant much higher quality images.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:08.15,0:04:10.84,1080P-sgsm-63,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}这意味着更高的图像质量
Dialogue: 0,0:04:11.04,0:04:13.68,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}The camera also allowed the changing of lenses
Dialogue: 0,0:04:11.04,0:04:13.68,1080P-sgsm-63,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}该相机还允许更换镜头
Dialogue: 0,0:04:13.68,0:04:16.63,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}and you could swap out film types between photos
Dialogue: 0,0:04:13.68,0:04:16.63,1080P-sgsm-63,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}而且你可以在照片之间更换不同类型的胶片
Dialogue: 0,0:04:16.79,0:04:19.93,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}and that would prove to be really useful on later missions.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:16.79,0:04:19.93,1080P-sgsm-63,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}而这在以后的任务中会被证明是非常有用的
Dialogue: 0,0:04:20.60,0:04:23.87,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}Again the cameras would be modified for flight into space.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:20.60,0:04:23.87,1080P-sgsm-63,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}同样的 这些相机也会被修改 以便飞向太空
Dialogue: 0,0:04:24.16,0:04:27.88,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}They had a waist level viewfinder and that didn't work in the Mercury capsule
Dialogue: 0,0:04:24.16,0:04:27.88,1080P-sgsm-63,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}它们有一个腰平取景器 但这在水星太空舱中无法使用
Dialogue: 0,0:04:27.90,0:04:30.87,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}so they took that out and just put a viewfinder on the side.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:27.90,0:04:30.87,1080P-sgsm-63,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}所以他们就把它拆掉了 只是在相机侧边放了一个取景器
Dialogue: 0,0:04:31.32,0:04:37.33,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}The film cartridges would be modified to hold many more frames of film.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:31.32,0:04:37.33,1080P-sgsm-63,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}胶卷盒被改装成可以容纳更多的胶片
Dialogue: 0,0:04:37.37,0:04:39.39,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}I think they use hundred frame rolls
Dialogue: 0,0:04:37.37,0:04:39.39,1080P-sgsm-63,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}我觉得他们用的是百格卷
Dialogue: 0,0:04:39.80,0:04:46.87,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}and they were locked closed so that they couldn't be accidentally opened in space.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:39.80,0:04:46.87,1080P-sgsm-63,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}而且是锁着的 这样就不会在太空中被意外打开
Dialogue: 0,0:04:47.12,0:04:48.92,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}The surface of course was leatherette.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:47.12,0:04:48.92,1080P-sgsm-63,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}当然 (原本)表面是皮革的
Dialogue: 0,0:04:48.94,0:04:51.75,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}They stripped that off and then painted everything black.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:48.94,0:04:51.75,1080P-sgsm-63,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}他们把它剥掉 然后把所有的东西都涂成黑色
Dialogue: 0,0:04:52.05,0:04:54.04,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}The engineers went and looked at
Dialogue: 0,0:04:52.05,0:04:54.04,1080P-sgsm-63,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}工程师们去看了看
Dialogue: 0,0:04:54.04,0:04:58.52,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}and they figured that they could machine off parts of the casing to reduce the mass.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:54.04,0:04:58.52,1080P-sgsm-63,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}而他们认为可以通过机械加工的方式来减少质量
Dialogue: 0,0:04:59.24,0:05:01.81,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}So yeah this camera would fly with Wally
Dialogue: 0,0:04:59.24,0:05:01.81,1080P-sgsm-63,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}那么没错 这台相机最终被沃利带上了天
Dialogue: 0,0:05:01.83,0:05:06.43,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}and then it would also fly with Gordon Cooper on the final Mercury flight.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:01.83,0:05:06.43,1080P-sgsm-63,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}然后它还会和戈登·库珀一起在水星号的最后一次飞行中使用
Dialogue: 0,0:05:06.88,0:05:10.16,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}And apparently the camera actually ended up in Gordon Cooper's possession
Dialogue: 0,0:05:06.88,0:05:10.16,1080P-sgsm-63,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}而很显然 这台相机最终还是落入到了戈登·库珀的手中
Dialogue: 0,0:05:10.16,0:05:16.56,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}and it would be later sold at auction for 275 000 dollars.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:10.16,0:05:16.56,1080P-sgsm-63,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}后来在拍卖会上以27.5万美元卖出
Dialogue: 0,0:05:16.77,0:05:19.48,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}But if you are a camera fan that want a replica
Dialogue: 0,0:05:16.77,0:05:19.48,1080P-sgsm-63,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}但如果你是一个相机迷 想要一个复制品
Dialogue: 0,0:05:19.52,0:05:26.16,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}there's a guy called Cole Rise who is making Hasselblad replicas for like five thousand dollars.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:19.52,0:05:26.16,1080P-sgsm-63,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}那么可以去看看Cole Rise 他会做哈苏相机的复制品 差不多要5000美元一台
Dialogue: 0,0:05:26.16,0:05:30.08,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}He has an amazing site where he's pretty much documented the whole process
Dialogue: 0,0:05:26.16,0:05:30.08,1080P-sgsm-63,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}他的网站很不错 在那里他几乎记录了你想了解的关于这些相机的
Dialogue: 0,0:05:30.10,0:05:33.40,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}and all the stuff you could ever want to know about a lot of these cameras.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:30.10,0:05:33.40,1080P-sgsm-63,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}整个过程以及各种各样的东西
Dialogue: 0,0:05:34.07,0:05:36.12,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}So anyway most significantly
Dialogue: 0,0:05:34.07,0:05:36.12,1080P-sgsm-63,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}那么无论如何 最重要的是
Dialogue: 0,0:05:36.14,0:05:40.70,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}this Hasselblad would set the standard for at least the decade to come and further.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:36.14,0:05:40.70,1080P-sgsm-63,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}这款哈苏相机将至少为未来十年甚至更远的时间里树立标准
Dialogue: 0,0:05:41.09,0:05:44.94,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}Hasselblad cameras became the camera used on GeminI and Apollo.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:41.09,0:05:44.94,1080P-sgsm-63,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}哈苏相机成为双子座和阿波罗计划中使用的相机
Dialogue: 0,0:05:45.71,0:05:51.32,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}They transitioned from simply taking photos out of windows to actually taking photos while on EVA
Dialogue: 0,0:05:45.71,0:05:51.32,1080P-sgsm-63,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}他们从简单的从窗外拍照过渡到在舱外活动(EVA)中进行拍照
Dialogue: 0,0:05:51.37,0:05:55.22,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}and yeah they took photo of Ed White on a spacewalk.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:51.37,0:05:55.22,1080P-sgsm-63,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}是的 他们拍到了爱德华·怀特在太空行走的照片
Dialogue: 0,0:05:55.60,0:05:59.82,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}At that point Hasselblad saw this and they realized that NASA were using their cameras
Dialogue: 0,0:05:55.60,0:05:59.82,1080P-sgsm-63,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}在那时 哈苏意识到NASA在使用他们的相机
Dialogue: 0,0:05:59.85,0:06:04.84,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}and they got in touch with NASA and began to work directly on cameras for the space program.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:59.85,0:06:04.84,1080P-sgsm-63,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}之后他们与NASA取得了联系 并开始直接为太空计划研发相机
Dialogue: 0,0:06:05.60,0:06:10.36,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}So for the lunar EVA they developed the 500 EL Data Camera
Dialogue: 0,0:06:05.60,0:06:10.36,1080P-sgsm-63,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}那么在月球EVA中 他们开发了500EL数据相机
Dialogue: 0,0:06:10.39,0:06:12.92,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}with a silver finish for thermal control.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:10.39,0:06:12.92,1080P-sgsm-63,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}为了更好的热控制而做成了银色的抛光表面
Dialogue: 0,0:06:13.28,0:06:15.68,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}They had a special low distortion lens
Dialogue: 0,0:06:13.28,0:06:15.68,1080P-sgsm-63,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}同时配备一个特殊的低失真镜头
Dialogue: 0,0:06:15.68,0:06:21.28,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}and they added the resole plate which is a sheet of glass with the grid of black reference crosses
Dialogue: 0,0:06:15.68,0:06:21.28,1080P-sgsm-63,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}而他们在那上面加了一块有黑色参考十字的网格玻璃板
Dialogue: 0,0:06:21.36,0:06:23.97,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}which were you know projected onto the image.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:21.36,0:06:23.97,1080P-sgsm-63,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}这样参考线就被投射到图像上
Dialogue: 0,0:06:24.08,0:06:29.12,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}So these of course were used for extracting measurements from the images off the lunar surface.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:24.08,0:06:29.12,1080P-sgsm-63,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}那么这些参考线当然是用来从月球表面的图像中提取测量值的
Dialogue: 0,0:06:29.14,0:06:33.33,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}This was an camera designed for science as well as pretty pictures.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:29.14,0:06:33.33,1080P-sgsm-63,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}这是一台同时为科学和亮丽照片而设计的相机
Dialogue: 0,0:06:34.16,0:06:39.28,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}So Hasselblad's 70 millimeter format would actually continue to be used after Apollo
Dialogue: 0,0:06:34.16,0:06:39.28,1080P-sgsm-63,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}那么哈苏的70毫米规格实际上在阿波罗之后还在继续使用
Dialogue: 0,0:06:39.42,0:06:42.77,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}through Skylab and well into the Shuttle era.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:39.42,0:06:42.77,1080P-sgsm-63,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}经过天空实验室 一直到航天飞机时代
Dialogue: 0,0:06:43.44,0:06:47.11,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}But rewinding a bit it was towards the end of the Apollo program
Dialogue: 0,0:06:43.44,0:06:47.11,1080P-sgsm-63,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}但是 回溯一下 在阿波罗计划的末期
Dialogue: 0,0:06:47.16,0:06:52.89,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}that NASA began to introduce the smaller 35 millimeter Nikon SLR cameras.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:47.16,0:06:52.89,1080P-sgsm-63,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}NASA开始使用更小的35毫米尼康单反相机
Dialogue: 0,0:06:53.72,0:06:56.67,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}Nikon began working directly with NASA at this time.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:53.72,0:06:56.67,1080P-sgsm-63,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}尼康在这个时候开始直接与NASA合作
Dialogue: 0,0:06:57.06,0:07:01.03,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}They would make customized versions of their cameras to NASA standards.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:57.06,0:07:01.03,1080P-sgsm-63,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}他们会按照NASA的标准来制作定制版的相机
Dialogue: 0,0:07:01.31,0:07:04.96,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}And their cameras actually continue to fly in space today.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:01.31,0:07:04.96,1080P-sgsm-63,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}而他们的相机实际上至今仍在太空中飞行
Dialogue: 0,0:07:05.75,0:07:10.49,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}Again they had to convert these consumer cameras to NASA requirements.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:05.75,0:07:10.49,1080P-sgsm-63,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}同样 他们必须把这些消费者相机按照NASA的要求进行改装
Dialogue: 0,0:07:10.73,0:07:15.82,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}The base cameras had the exterior level removed and they were simply painted matte black.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:10.73,0:07:15.82,1080P-sgsm-63,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}首先是去掉了原型相机的外壳 并被简单地涂成了亚光黑色
Dialogue: 0,0:07:16.24,0:07:20.49,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}NASA stipulated that they had to have special vacuum safe lubricants.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:16.24,0:07:20.49,1080P-sgsm-63,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}NASA规定 他们必须使用特殊的可用于真空的润滑剂
Dialogue: 0,0:07:20.80,0:07:23.03,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}They had different soldering standards.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:20.80,0:07:23.03,1080P-sgsm-63,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}同时 相机的焊接标准也进行了修改
Dialogue: 0,0:07:23.03,0:07:25.68,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}Many of the plastic parts were replaced by metal.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:23.03,0:07:25.68,1080P-sgsm-63,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}许多塑料部件都被金属替代了
Dialogue: 0,0:07:26.16,0:07:31.15,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}And the film transport mechanism had to handle the thinner polyester film used by NASA
Dialogue: 0,0:07:26.16,0:07:31.15,1080P-sgsm-63,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}同时需要确保胶片传输机构能够使用NASA较薄的聚酯纤维胶片
Dialogue: 0,0:07:31.47,0:07:35.39,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}and that meant of course that they could fit many more photos onto a roll of film.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:31.47,0:07:35.39,1080P-sgsm-63,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}(NASA之所以使用较薄的胶片) 当然是为了在同样的胶卷中容纳更多的胶片
Dialogue: 0,0:07:36.26,0:07:41.47,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}And of course there were many exterior modifications to make the cameras easier to use.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:36.26,0:07:41.47,1080P-sgsm-63,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}当然也有许多外观上的修改 使相机更易使用
Dialogue: 0,0:07:41.59,0:07:44.20,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}You know larger controls, removal of strap lugs.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:41.59,0:07:44.20,1080P-sgsm-63,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}会有更大的控制机构 同时去掉用于吊带的挂环
Dialogue: 0,0:07:44.30,0:07:48.73,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}Because having a camera on a strap around your neck doesn't make sense in 0g.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:44.30,0:07:48.73,1080P-sgsm-63,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}因为在失重的情况下 没法把相机通过带子挂在脖子上
Dialogue: 0,0:07:49.10,0:07:52.46,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}And modifications of the viewfinder to make it work through a spacesuit.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:49.10,0:07:52.46,1080P-sgsm-63,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}还有对取景器的修改 这样即使穿着宇航服也能使用
Dialogue: 0,0:07:52.80,0:07:55.59,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}Now I don't have time to go into any of the detail on this
Dialogue: 0,0:07:52.80,0:07:55.59,1080P-sgsm-63,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}那么我没时间去细说这些了
Dialogue: 0,0:07:55.64,0:08:00.21,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}but Timm Chapman is a camera collector who owns several NASA Nikons
Dialogue: 0,0:07:55.64,0:08:00.21,1080P-sgsm-63,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}但蒂姆-查普曼是一个相机收藏家 他拥有几台NASA的尼康相机
Dialogue: 0,0:08:00.22,0:08:04.47,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}and he's done a lot of research writing some white papers on the modifications
Dialogue: 0,0:08:00.22,0:08:04.47,1080P-sgsm-63,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}他做了很多研究 写了一些关于这些改装细节的报告
Dialogue: 0,0:08:04.47,0:08:07.68,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}as well as compiling the serial numbers of the NASA hardware.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:04.47,0:08:07.68,1080P-sgsm-63,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}以及编写NASA设备的序列号
Dialogue: 0,0:08:07.68,0:08:12.88,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}If you want to know any more detail on the NASA Nikons his site is the place to go.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:07.68,0:08:12.88,1080P-sgsm-63,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}如果你想知道NASA尼康相机的任何更多细节 可以去访问他的网站
Dialogue: 0,0:08:13.54,0:08:19.36,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}So yeah the first NASA approved Nikon flown was a modified Nikon F SLR
Dialogue: 0,0:08:13.54,0:08:19.36,1080P-sgsm-63,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}那么第一个NASA批准上天的尼康相机是一个改装过的尼康F单反
Dialogue: 0,0:08:19.36,0:08:21.66,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}and it was flown on Apollo 15.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:19.36,0:08:21.66,1080P-sgsm-63,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}这在阿波罗15号上得到使用
Dialogue: 0,0:08:21.97,0:08:24.76,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}It was part of an experiment to observe space dust.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:21.97,0:08:24.76,1080P-sgsm-63,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}它是观察空间尘埃实验的一部分
Dialogue: 0,0:08:24.96,0:08:27.57,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}When the command module was in the shadow of the moon
Dialogue: 0,0:08:24.96,0:08:27.57,1080P-sgsm-63,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}当指令舱处在月球的阴影中时
Dialogue: 0,0:08:27.68,0:08:31.03,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}they would be pointed out the window and take a number of photos.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:27.68,0:08:31.03,1080P-sgsm-63,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}将相机指向窗外 拍下不少照片
Dialogue: 0,0:08:31.03,0:08:34.76,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}Unfortunately there was an error in the coordinate systems
Dialogue: 0,0:08:31.03,0:08:34.76,1080P-sgsm-63,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}不幸的是 坐标系统出现了错误
Dialogue: 0,0:08:34.78,0:08:37.83,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}and they ended up pointing the camera at the wrong part of the sky.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:34.78,0:08:37.83,1080P-sgsm-63,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}结果他们把相机进行了错误的指向 拍摄了天空中的其他区域
Dialogue: 0,0:08:38.56,0:08:43.77,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}For Skylab they continued to use the same Nikon F but they added a motorized drive to it.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:38.56,0:08:43.77,1080P-sgsm-63,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}在天空实验室 他们继续使用同样的尼康F 但增加了一个电动驱动装置
Dialogue: 0,0:08:43.98,0:08:46.88,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}It was used to photograph Earth through windows.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:43.98,0:08:46.88,1080P-sgsm-63,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}这台相机被用来通过窗户拍摄地球
Dialogue: 0,0:08:46.94,0:08:49.24,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}It was used with filters to study earth's atmosphere
Dialogue: 0,0:08:46.94,0:08:49.24,1080P-sgsm-63,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}并搭配滤镜来研究地球的大气
Dialogue: 0,0:08:49.24,0:08:53.00,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}and to check that the corona. This solar telescope was working.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:49.24,0:08:53.00,1080P-sgsm-63,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}同时还能查看日冕 作为一台太阳望远镜
Dialogue: 0,0:08:54.39,0:08:56.95,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}By the time the Space Shuttle program came around
Dialogue: 0,0:08:54.39,0:08:56.95,1080P-sgsm-63,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}到了航天飞机计划的时候
Dialogue: 0,0:08:56.95,0:08:59.20,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}they'd moved on to the Nikon F3.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:56.95,0:08:59.20,1080P-sgsm-63,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}他们已经换代到尼康F3上了
Dialogue: 0,0:08:59.20,0:09:03.83,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}And depending upon mission requirements they had a small version and a large version.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:59.20,0:09:03.83,1080P-sgsm-63,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}根据任务要求 会使用一个较小版本或一个较大版本
Dialogue: 0,0:09:03.99,0:09:09.51,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}The large version handled 250 exposures which was quite massive.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:03.99,0:09:09.51,1080P-sgsm-63,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}较大的版本可以进行250次曝光 这个能力相当不错
Dialogue: 0,0:09:10.00,0:09:12.88,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}The F3 would also be used on EVAs.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:10.00,0:09:12.88,1080P-sgsm-63,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}F3也将被用于EVA
Dialogue: 0,0:09:12.93,0:09:17.32,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}So it went outside. It would be covered by thermal blankets to stabilize the temperature.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:12.93,0:09:17.32,1080P-sgsm-63,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}那么这台相机会暴露在外太空 这样它会被隔热毯覆盖以稳定温度
Dialogue: 0,0:09:17.49,0:09:23.26,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}and you can actually see one attached to Bruce McCandless MMU when he's free flying in space.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:17.49,0:09:23.26,1080P-sgsm-63,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}{\fs55}当布鲁斯·麦坎德勒斯在太空中自由飞行时 实际上你可以看到一台这样的相机连接到他的MMU
Dialogue: 0,0:09:23.58,0:09:27.96,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}Of course the camera that took this image was a 70 millimeter Hasselblad.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:23.58,0:09:27.96,1080P-sgsm-63,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}当然 拍摄这张照片的相机是70毫米的哈苏
Dialogue: 0,0:09:28.95,0:09:32.32,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}So the next big step forward would be in 1991
Dialogue: 0,0:09:28.95,0:09:32.32,1080P-sgsm-63,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}那么下一个大的进步是在1991年
Dialogue: 0,0:09:32.36,0:09:37.86,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}with the flight of the Nikon F4 ESC, Electronic Still Camera.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:32.36,0:09:37.86,1080P-sgsm-63,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}随着尼康F4无反相机的升空
Dialogue: 0,0:09:38.12,0:09:41.31,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}This began the transition to digital photography.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:38.12,0:09:41.31,1080P-sgsm-63,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}由此开始了向数码摄影的过渡
Dialogue: 0,0:09:41.51,0:09:45.27,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}This camera was built out of a regular F4 SLR body
Dialogue: 0,0:09:41.51,0:09:45.27,1080P-sgsm-63,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}这款相机是在普通的F4单反机身的基础上制造出来的
Dialogue: 0,0:09:45.27,0:09:51.12,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}but with a 1024, 1024 8-bit monochrome image sensor in the focal plane.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:45.27,0:09:51.12,1080P-sgsm-63,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}但在焦平面上有一个1024 x 1024(约105万像素)的8位的单色图像传感器
Dialogue: 0,0:09:51.17,0:09:55.34,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}The sensor had actually originally been developed for use on the Hubble Space Telescope.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:51.17,0:09:55.34,1080P-sgsm-63,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}这个传感器最初实际上是为哈勃太空望远镜开发的
Dialogue: 0,0:09:55.60,0:09:57.36,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}So the camera was bulky.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:55.60,0:09:57.36,1080P-sgsm-63,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}那么这台相机很笨重
Dialogue: 0,0:09:57.36,0:09:59.44,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}It stored images to a hard disk.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:57.36,0:09:59.44,1080P-sgsm-63,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}它将图像存储在硬盘上
Dialogue: 0,0:09:59.48,0:10:03.85,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}But it was hugely advantageous to be able to transmit the images to the ground
Dialogue: 0,0:09:59.48,0:10:03.85,1080P-sgsm-63,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}但能够将图像传输到地面是非常有利的
Dialogue: 0,0:10:04.21,0:10:08.24,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}where they would get processed by a pixar image computer and print it out.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:04.21,0:10:08.24,1080P-sgsm-63,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}这样 图像就会被(地面的)皮克斯图像电脑进行处理 并打印出来
Dialogue: 0,0:10:08.24,0:10:09.83,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}And this was especially useful.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:08.24,0:10:09.83,1080P-sgsm-63,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}而这会特别有用
Dialogue: 0,0:10:09.83,0:10:13.05,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}Say if you're on a mission, you've grabbed a satellite from space
Dialogue: 0,0:10:09.83,0:10:13.05,1080P-sgsm-63,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}比如说如果你在执行任务 你从太空中抓到了一颗卫星
Dialogue: 0,0:10:13.08,0:10:16.02,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}and you need help from the ground to solve problems.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:13.08,0:10:16.02,1080P-sgsm-63,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}而你需要地面的帮助来解决问题
Dialogue: 0,0:10:16.06,0:10:18.38,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}You know, a picture literally is a thousand words.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:16.06,0:10:18.38,1080P-sgsm-63,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}很明显 一张图片所蕴含的信息量真的很大
Dialogue: 0,0:10:19.44,0:10:22.80,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}There was a second digital camera floating around the same time.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:19.44,0:10:22.80,1080P-sgsm-63,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}同一时间 还有第二款数码相机在太空中使用
Dialogue: 0,0:10:22.80,0:10:26.24,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}It was developed by Kodak and known as the Hawkeye II
Dialogue: 0,0:10:22.80,0:10:26.24,1080P-sgsm-63,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}它是由柯达公司开发的 被称为鹰眼二代
Dialogue: 0,0:10:26.24,0:10:28.56,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}and while it only flew in a single test flight
Dialogue: 0,0:10:26.24,0:10:28.56,1080P-sgsm-63,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}虽然它只进行了一次测试使用
Dialogue: 0,0:10:28.56,0:10:33.04,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}it did actually end up being the basis for Kodak's DCS 100
Dialogue: 0,0:10:28.56,0:10:33.04,1080P-sgsm-63,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}但它实际上最终成为了柯达DCS 100的基础
Dialogue: 0,0:10:33.17,0:10:36.42,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}which is arguably the first commercial digital SLR.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:33.17,0:10:36.42,1080P-sgsm-63,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}可以说是第一台商用数码单反相机
Dialogue: 0,0:10:37.61,0:10:42.19,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}Both cameras were actually being tested for an interesting payload called Hercules
Dialogue: 0,0:10:37.61,0:10:42.19,1080P-sgsm-63,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}这两款相机实际上都是在测试一个有趣的有效载荷 叫大力神
Dialogue: 0,0:10:42.52,0:10:47.33,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}which would use inertial measurement units attached to the camera to measure the orientation.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:42.52,0:10:47.33,1080P-sgsm-63,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}它将使用附着在相机上的惯性测量单位(IMU)来测量方位
Dialogue: 0,0:10:47.65,0:10:51.22,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}So it could tag images with their longitude and latitude on the ground.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:47.65,0:10:51.22,1080P-sgsm-63,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}因此 它可以在地面上用经度和纬度标记图像
Dialogue: 0,0:10:51.37,0:10:54.03,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}The system would take the orbit of the Space Shuttle
Dialogue: 0,0:10:51.37,0:10:54.03,1080P-sgsm-63,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}该系统将以航天飞机的轨道为基准
Dialogue: 0,0:10:54.16,0:10:57.54,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}and then the astronaut would align the camera with some reference stars
Dialogue: 0,0:10:54.16,0:10:57.54,1080P-sgsm-63,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}然后宇航员会将相机与一些参考星对准
Dialogue: 0,0:10:57.55,0:11:02.55,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}and then after that the system could figure out where the camera was being pointed thanks to the IMU.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:57.55,0:11:02.55,1080P-sgsm-63,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}而后 系统可以计算出相机的指向 这就得归功于IMU了
Dialogue: 0,0:11:02.56,0:11:06.24,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}Now my phone has an IMU in it and it's the size of a tiny microchip
Dialogue: 0,0:11:02.56,0:11:06.24,1080P-sgsm-63,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}现在我的手机里就有一个IMU 它的大小类似于一个小小的微芯片
Dialogue: 0,0:11:06.27,0:11:10.21,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}but back then the IMUs were huge physical gyroscopes that
Dialogue: 0,0:11:06.27,0:11:10.21,1080P-sgsm-63,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}但当时的IMU是巨大的物理陀螺仪
Dialogue: 0,0:11:10.41,0:11:14.57,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}and if you look in the photo it's that big cylinder attached to the bottom of the camera there.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:10.41,0:11:14.57,1080P-sgsm-63,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}如果你看照片 就是那个连接到相机底部的大圆筒
Dialogue: 0,0:11:15.93,0:11:21.02,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}So the first commercial digital camera used in space was apparently the DCS 460
Dialogue: 0,0:11:15.93,0:11:21.02,1080P-sgsm-63,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}那么第一台在太空中使用的商用数码相机显然是DCS 460
Dialogue: 0,0:11:21.37,0:11:24.67,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}which was again a Nikon body with a digital back
Dialogue: 0,0:11:21.37,0:11:24.67,1080P-sgsm-63,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}这又是一个带数码后背的尼康机身
Dialogue: 0,0:11:24.94,0:11:28.83,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}and I think the whole thing cost something like twenty eight thousand dollars
Dialogue: 0,0:11:24.94,0:11:28.83,1080P-sgsm-63,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}我想这整个机器的成本大概是两万八千美元左右
Dialogue: 0,0:11:29.07,0:11:33.67,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}but for that you got six megapixels of color imagery at 12 bits per pixel
Dialogue: 0,0:11:29.07,0:11:33.67,1080P-sgsm-63,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}但你得到了600万像素 每像素12位色深的彩色图像
Dialogue: 0,0:11:34.02,0:11:37.14,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}and the ability to take an image every 12 seconds.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:34.02,0:11:37.14,1080P-sgsm-63,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}以及每12秒拍摄一张图像的能力
Dialogue: 0,0:11:37.39,0:11:44.20,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}They could fit 42 images on the 260 megabyte hard drives that would fit into their PC slot.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:37.39,0:11:44.20,1080P-sgsm-63,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}这可以在260兆字节(MB)的硬盘上装下42张图像 而硬盘可以装进电脑插槽
Dialogue: 0,0:11:44.88,0:11:49.44,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}Over time of course they'd upgrade. They had the DCS 660, the 760.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:44.88,0:11:49.44,1080P-sgsm-63,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}随着时间的推移 当然会进行升级 比如DCS 660和DCS 760
Dialogue: 0,0:11:49.44,0:11:52.75,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}They got better and cheaper thanks to moore's law.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:49.44,0:11:52.75,1080P-sgsm-63,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}由于摩尔定律 它们变得更好更便宜
Dialogue: 0,0:11:52.95,0:11:54.48,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}And it's also worth noting that
Dialogue: 0,0:11:52.95,0:11:54.48,1080P-sgsm-63,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}而且值得注意的是
Dialogue: 0,0:11:54.48,0:11:59.44,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}these digital cameras were actually still based on the Nikon F-series bodies.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:54.48,0:11:59.44,1080P-sgsm-63,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}这些数码相机实际上还是基于尼康F系列机身的
Dialogue: 0,0:11:59.63,0:12:03.64,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}So astronauts who used one would be sort of familiar with the other.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:59.63,0:12:03.64,1080P-sgsm-63,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}所以宇航员用过其中的一台就会对另一台比较熟悉
Dialogue: 0,0:12:03.90,0:12:10.07,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}In fact sometimes you'll see astronauts refer to the DCS 760 as the digital F5
Dialogue: 0,0:12:03.90,0:12:10.07,1080P-sgsm-63,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}事实上 有时你会看到宇航员把DCS 760称为数码版F5
Dialogue: 0,0:12:10.80,0:12:15.68,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}which brings me to the last film camera used by NASA in space.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:10.80,0:12:15.68,1080P-sgsm-63,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}这让我想到了NASA在太空中使用的最后一台胶片相机
Dialogue: 0,0:12:16.00,0:12:20.86,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}The Nikon F5 and it made its debut on Endeavour in 1998.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:16.00,0:12:20.86,1080P-sgsm-63,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}也就是尼康F5 其在1998年首次在奋进号上使用
Dialogue: 0,0:12:21.12,0:12:25.95,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}By this point Nikon had incorporated most of NASA's requirements into their regular production
Dialogue: 0,0:12:21.12,0:12:25.95,1080P-sgsm-63,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}此时尼康已经将NASA的大部分要求纳入了他们的常规产品当中
Dialogue: 0,0:12:25.98,0:12:29.16,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}so the cameras were almost identical to those in stores.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:25.98,0:12:29.16,1080P-sgsm-63,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}所以相机和商店里卖的几乎是一样的
Dialogue: 0,0:12:29.63,0:12:33.95,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}These were carried on EVAs and were something of a step up from the F3
Dialogue: 0,0:12:29.63,0:12:33.95,1080P-sgsm-63,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}这些相机是在EVA上携带的 是F3的升级版
Dialogue: 0,0:12:33.97,0:12:36.27,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}since they added auto focus capability.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:33.97,0:12:36.27,1080P-sgsm-63,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}因为他们增加了自动对焦功能
Dialogue: 0,0:12:36.30,0:12:39.80,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}There's a lot of out out-of-focus shots from you know spacewalks.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:36.30,0:12:39.80,1080P-sgsm-63,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}(这是因为)在太空行走中拍摄的照片很多都失焦了
Dialogue: 0,0:12:40.88,0:12:43.04,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}Nowadays of course everything is digital.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:40.88,0:12:43.04,1080P-sgsm-63,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}现在当然一切都数字化了
Dialogue: 0,0:12:43.04,0:12:44.80,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}According to wikipedia
Dialogue: 0,0:12:43.04,0:12:44.80,1080P-sgsm-63,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}根据维基百科
Dialogue: 0,0:12:44.99,0:12:49.95,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}there's at least 10 types of Nikon digital SLR that have been used on the space station.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:44.99,0:12:49.95,1080P-sgsm-63,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}至少有10种尼康数码单反在空间站上使用过
Dialogue: 0,0:12:50.39,0:12:54.52,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}The current NASA standard I believe is the Nikon D5.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:50.39,0:12:54.52,1080P-sgsm-63,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}目前NASA的标准我相信是尼康D5
Dialogue: 0,0:12:55.12,0:12:58.80,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}But you know the advantages of instant feedback are one thing
Dialogue: 0,0:12:55.12,0:12:58.80,1080P-sgsm-63,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}但即时反馈的优势只是数码相机的一个特点 {\fs55}(不是说没有这个优势你就不能用胶片了)
Dialogue: 0,0:12:58.85,0:13:00.92,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}but even if you want to use film
Dialogue: 0,0:12:58.85,0:13:00.92,1080P-sgsm-63,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}但即使你想用胶片
Dialogue: 0,0:13:01.20,0:13:04.78,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}there's this problem that missions to the space station last month.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:01.20,0:13:04.78,1080P-sgsm-63,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}有这样一个问题 那就是空间站的任务一般都持续数月
Dialogue: 0,0:13:04.80,0:13:07.92,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}And because of the higher radiation in low earth orbit
Dialogue: 0,0:13:04.80,0:13:07.92,1080P-sgsm-63,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}由于近地轨道的辐射较高
Dialogue: 0,0:13:08.02,0:13:10.71,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}the film fogs up from radiation exposure.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:08.02,0:13:10.71,1080P-sgsm-63,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}胶片会因为辐射的曝光而模糊
Dialogue: 0,0:13:10.72,0:13:13.66,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}And that's a problem that never mattered as much on the Space Shuttle
Dialogue: 0,0:13:10.72,0:13:13.66,1080P-sgsm-63,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}而这个问题在航天飞机并没有这么严重
Dialogue: 0,0:13:13.67,0:13:16.14,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}because it only stayed in orbit for a couple of weeks.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:13.67,0:13:16.14,1080P-sgsm-63,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}因为它只在轨道上呆几个星期
Dialogue: 0,0:13:16.76,0:13:20.24,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}Skylab actually had a radiation hardened film vault
Dialogue: 0,0:13:16.76,0:13:20.24,1080P-sgsm-63,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}而天空实验室实际上有一个防辐射的胶片储藏室
Dialogue: 0,0:13:20.24,0:13:22.39,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}and that's so that they could protect it.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:20.24,0:13:22.39,1080P-sgsm-63,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}而这样就可以保护胶片不被辐射曝光
Dialogue: 0,0:13:22.49,0:13:25.04,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}And when Skylab broke up and re-entry
Dialogue: 0,0:13:22.49,0:13:25.04,1080P-sgsm-63,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}而在天空实验室解体再入的时候
Dialogue: 0,0:13:25.24,0:13:28.89,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}some of the biggest chunks of debris that made it to the surface were the vaults.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:25.24,0:13:28.89,1080P-sgsm-63,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}残骸中最大的一些块状物抵达了地面 其中就包括这个胶片储藏室的部分
Dialogue: 0,0:13:29.68,0:13:35.56,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}On the other hand, cameras on the ISS can get permanent bad pixels from radiation damage
Dialogue: 0,0:13:29.68,0:13:35.56,1080P-sgsm-63,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}另一方面 国际空间站上的相机会因辐射损伤而产生永久的坏像素
Dialogue: 0,0:13:35.59,0:13:38.38,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}so it's not all good news for being digital in space.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:35.59,0:13:38.38,1080P-sgsm-63,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}所以在太空中使用数字技术也不是尽善尽美的
Dialogue: 0,0:13:38.63,0:13:42.30,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}But I don't see that as a technical argument for returning to film.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:38.63,0:13:42.30,1080P-sgsm-63,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}但我不认为这是回归胶片的技术论据
Dialogue: 0,0:13:42.80,0:13:46.07,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}Ultimately as the cost of space travel drops
Dialogue: 0,0:13:42.80,0:13:46.07,1080P-sgsm-63,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}最终随着太空旅行成本的下降
Dialogue: 0,0:13:46.07,0:13:48.16,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}and we start to see some space tours.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:46.07,0:13:48.16,1080P-sgsm-63,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}我们会看到一些太空旅游开始进行
Dialogue: 0,0:13:48.16,0:13:53.44,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}Maybe we'll see some of them deciding to return to film again for artistic reasons.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:48.16,0:13:53.44,1080P-sgsm-63,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}也许其中一些太空游客 会因为艺术的原因而重新使用胶片摄影
Dialogue: 0,0:13:53.86,0:13:56.43,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}I'm Scott Manley. Fly safe.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:53.86,0:13:56.43,1080P-sgsm-63,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}我是Scott Manley 切记 注意飞行安全
